Erik:
Two decades of existing in defiance of all good sense.

How many chickens does it take open a checking account?
3
Yeah, I'm not sure how or why but that's all it takes to deceive a bank teller. I mean, you can do the same thing with one horse and a fake mustache but the gig is up if the horse craps in the middle of the account meeting, so it's always a little iffy.

Now that I have my schedule for next year all plotted out I can move on to the next phase of my obsessive plans, heckling my future teachers to get my hands on the reading lists. I can finally put my lurking skills to good use.
Almost twelve hours of sleep makes for a very blithe Erik. I wonder what this monster will be, I hope it's not a manticore...

Someday, when there is nothing left to believe in, we will ask each other, "was it worth it?"
And in that moment we will know if we wasted our lives and if there is any reason to believe in tomorrow.
Maybe I did love him, or maybe I was so lonely that wanting love became feeling love and knowing the difference no longer mattered.
If this is all there is to living, why is dying so painful? Why do we cling to the mortal coil if doubt is the end result?
Maybe I missed the point, maybe I was blind to God's love.
If beauty is the divine, then why does the snow flake fall from Heaven?
Why does the snow flake melt when I touch it?
Why can't I find Him now?
Show me, show me where I failed.

I've been at Lawrence since Sunday. I've completed my move into Kohler and have bought the appropriate accoutrements for living in such a place, i.e. an 18-inch commercial grade fan (it is exceedingly powerful). I have to say I like my new dwelling, not alot of floor space but it is enough to keep me happy. It's been a little lonesome here, everyone I know here is busy, and now I'm busy because I work at Downer. I was there for over six hours yesterday, I showered twice. My giant painting is back in my possession, I wish to complete and add a more realistic feel to it. Well, as realistic as it can get...
I want everyone else back.

I had lunch with Professor McQuinn today. It was nice, we walked a little before hand and went menu hopping. I've come to realize I'm addicted to Vanilla Coke.

I had a dream not long ago, I was starring at a mirror and saw that all my hair had turned gray, except for the red in beard, which was pure white. I didn't look sad, just tired.

I don't want to go to work right now.
Good bye.

Haku

I'm leaving tomorrow morning for Colorado and I won't be back until next Friday. To everyone I owe drabbles I'm afraid you'll have to wait until I get back for your result's. I have begun the FMA/Inu crossover story and the drabble about buying Rin's clothes. I have also started some stuff on the drawing of Vash, but I should tell you now that it will mostly just be a master copy of a drawing in the comic, I'm not good enough to draw him freehand (do you know ho many details go into that man's jacket?).

So yesterday... I am so glad I am essentially done with work. I am so tired of having to watch adults become belligerent children once they get inside of a paddle boat. After work I shaved my head. I managed to do a pretty good job by myself, though my sister had to touch up a few places in the back. Then there was the cross country alumni race and picnic. It was fun, though I did feel out of place. Then again I never really did fit in to the higher cliques of the team but oh well, I was still glad to see them.

Then there was Rachel's party. Oh the decadence, oh the exuberance, oh the sticking money down Rachel's cleavage. I had a great time hanging out with everyone, managed to get some witty conversations in with just about everyone, I think. It was good to see Eric again. I'm less afraid now because of it. I didn't drink last night and it didn't make things awkward. Well, it was interesting to see my friends in the various stages of inebriation, and I didn't mind being part of the "sober up" squad, but I I guess there was the occasional moment of "Wow I guess he has had a lot tonight." I don't think Doug has ever been more affectionate towards me than he was tonight, and I mean it purely in the "hey buddy, how's it going?" sense, nothing more. Most of the new people I met last night seemed cool. Simon bit me, Bridget, and a few other people. Speaking of Bridget- Jenny, Eric's Bridget says "hi." I'm glad people liked my hat. I'm sorry if I worried you Rachel, I was having a great time regardless of how sober I was. I left somewhere around 12:30. Even though I was still in good spirits I was suddenly gripped by the need to run once I got off Rachel's property, so I did. I didn't run far but I felt like there was this pent of ball of energy that had to be released so I just followed that feeling. It was a great night for a full moon. I think I clocked in the most time spent dancing at the party. Good bye everyone. See you next week. Have a safe trip if you're going back to school.

Ok, I just read the latest "Trigun Maximum" and it was good, really good. I actually had to sit back for a minute and catch my breath after reading it (see I can continue my sexless existence so long as I have graphic novels like this one). So many loose ends have been ties up, there was angst (but the good kind, the plot driving kind), major ass kicking by Wolfwood and Vash, and Legato officially creeped me out for the first time in a long while. I won't ruin it for you, but let's just say he and Gene Simmons have at least thing in common now.
Other exciting Trigun news:
I saw the latest PVC models of Trigun characters and Legato's was pretty awesome. I may have to ask for it for Christmas.
I might be going out tonight, yay.
Bye y'all.

Today has been a rather lazy Sunday. Nothing really happened and things stayed pretty calm. I've been hitting the WoW pretty hard and have successfully completed my first dungeon (raise arms in a feeble effort at celebrating but am subverted by own tiredness).
I do not look forward to tomorrow,I really am starting to hate my job. I'm simply glad that I only have two real weeks of work left and then I go on several vacations and relax a week or two before coming back to Lawrence.
Beth, Rachel, Michelle; I really want to see you guys before I leave. I've seen a few people form Maine West this summer, but you guys have been the most notable exceptions. I like tuna...
Good night all.
7

Before I say anything else I would like to clarify yesterday's post. Yes I saw the new Willy Wonka movie, at IMAX no less, and it was fantastic. I loved watching Willy Wonka walk into glass doors. You really feel like Johnny Depp is harasing you with his face!

Today has been a full day, not productive, but full none the less. I play much WoW today. Went into the Deadmines, upgraded my armor and spells, felt ripped off by the auction house- a good time had by all.

After that I went to go visit Jason in the hospital. It was a harrowing journey involving trains and an automobile. Sadly no planes were present in this journey... Oh well, I managed to navigate my way pretty well through the city and got to his room with little trouble. Jason looked pretty well, despite not having a colon... I pray for his well being and the continuation of his quick recovery, which will hopefully include his safe journey home tomorrow if things go as desired (knock on wood). After that I traveled back to the Metra station, where I had to wait for an hour and a half for my last train. Food courts are boring if you don't eat.

That's all for now. Get better Jason. I will continue my stance on not tackling you for the sake of your recovery.
Bye.
Do you know what it feels like to be enveloped by Johnny Depp's face? It's like he's burrowing into your chest and you feel him writhing around inside you. It's almost too much to bear...
